        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/2–145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of State to the Acting Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Malta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-01">February 1,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cricket<note n="46" xml:id="d144fn46">Series designation for telegrams from the
                        Malta Conference. For record of the conference at Malta, January 30–February
                        2, 1945, between President Roosevelt and British Prime Minister Churchill,
                        with their advisers, see <ref target="frus1945Malta#pg_459">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conferences at Malta and Yalta</hi>, 1945, pp.
                            459</ref>–<ref target="frus1945Malta#pg_546">546</ref>
                    </note> 45. Have dispatched the following to Winant after conference which Eden
                    and I had with General Marshall<note n="47" xml:id="d144fn47">General of the
                        Army George C. Marshall, Chief of Staff, U.S. Army</note> and Field Marshal
                    Sir Alan Brooke.<note n="48" xml:id="d144fn48">Chief of the British Imperial
                        General Staff</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“You are authorized immediately to inform the European Advisory Commission of
                        this Government’s approval of the protocol on zones of occupation for
                        Germany. Eden is likewise telegraphing the British Government’s
                        approval.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Please advise McCloy.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
